The paper deals with designing codes for reliable and deniable communication over a noisy channel, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also mentions computational complexity and tractability, which suggests that it may also belong to the complexity theory (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with communication security, which could also place it in the cyber security (cs.CY) sub-category.
